erarchy\n   - Accessible navigation with ARIA labels\n\n2. Navbar ✅\n   - Logo on the left\n   - Navigation links centered\n   - Mobile hamburger menu toggle\n   - CTA button on the right\n\n3. Hero Section ✅\n   - Headline: \"Accelerate Your Development Workflow\"\n   - Subheadline explaining core value proposition\n   - Dual CTA buttons\n   - Hero image generated using the specified prompt\n\n4. Features Grid ✅\n   - 6 feature cards\n   - 3-column layout (responsive)\n   - Each card with icon, title, and description\n\n5. Pricing Table ✅\n   - 3 distinct tiers: Startup, Growth (recommended), Enterprise\n   - Consistent card design\n   - Pricing, feature list, and CTA for each tier\n\n6. Testimonials Section ✅\n   - 3 testimonial cards\n   - Customer quotes with names and titles\n\n7. Footer ✅\n   - 4-column layout with product, company, resources, and legal links\n   - Copyright notice\n   - Social media links\n\n8. Accessibility Considerations ✅\n   - ARIA labels\n   - Semantic markup\n   - Keyboard-navigable structure\n\n9. Performance ✅\n   - Deferred JavaScript\n   - Lazy loading for hero image\n   - Google Fonts with `display=swap`\n\nAdditional Notes:\n- Generated a hero image using the specified desi\n\n### CSS Worker — error\nERROR: Provider returned error\n\n### JS Worker — ok\nI've created the `app.js` file with interactive JavaScript enhancements for the Stackr landing page. Let me break down the implementation:\n\n### 1. Mobile Menu Toggle\n- Targets the `.mobile-menu-toggle` button and `#nav-menu`\n- Toggles `aria-expanded` attribute for accessibility\n- Adds/removes `active` class to show/hide mobile menu\n- Ensures the toggle works only if both elements exist\n\n### 2. Smooth Scrolling\n- Selects all anchor links starting with `#`\n- Prevents default link behavior\n- Uses `scrollIntoView()` with smooth behavior\n- Closes mobile menu after navigation (if open)\n\n### 3. Optional Hover Effects\n- Adds hover effects to pricing and feature cards\n- Uses