ty checks:\n- Color contrast ratios meet WCAG guidelines\n- Keyboard navigation supported\n- Screen reader friendly markup\n\n### Cross-Reference Checks\n✅ Verified alignment between design spec, HTML, CSS, and JS:\n- Color usage consistent\n- Typography implemented as specified\n- Responsive breakpoints match design\n\n### Detailed Report\nI've generated a comprehensive `test_report.json` that captures all valid\n\n\n## Files Created\n- `design_spec.md`: # Stackr Design Specification\n- `hero-image.png`: PNG image\n- `index.html`: <!DOCTYPE html>\n- `index_screenshot.png`: PNG image\n- `styles.css`: /* Root variables for design tokens */\n- `app.js`: document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {\n- `test_report.json`: {\n\n\n## Tester Issues\n- [warning] `index.html`: Named entity expected. Potential minor HTML validation issue.\n\n\n## Guidelines\n- Group results by worker: UX/Content, HTML, CSS, JavaScript, Testing\n- Include a summary table at the top with worker name, status (ok/error), and a one-liner\n- List all files created with their descriptions\n- Highlight any tester issues prominently\n- If the tester found issues, note which workers need fixes\n- If all workers succeeded, celebrate the output quality\n- Keep the report concise but complete\n\nOutput the full Markdown report.", "meta": {}}
